# Job Portal MVP (zero-cost)


Requirements: Node.js, npm, MongoDB (local or Atlas), Ollama (optional) or alternate local LLM.


1) Start MongoDB or create Atlas free cluster and set MONGO_URI in server/.env
2) Run server:
cd server
npm install
npm start
<!-- nZSbeOBIvuIgtrsG
akankshaofficial360_db_user -->
<!-- mongodb+srv://akankshaofficial360_db_user:nZSbeOBIvuIgtrsG@cluster0.wvvdv7v.mongodb.net/?appName=Cluster0 -->
3) Start extractor (needs local LLM like Ollama or replace call with HF):
cd extractor
npm install express node-fetch body-parser
node extract.js


4) Start crawler:
cd crawler
npm install playwright node-fetch
node index.js


5) Start frontend (any static host):
cd frontend
npm install
npm start


Notes:
- If you don't have Ollama, modify extractor/extract.js's callOllama to use a simpler extraction or HF Inference.
- Keep polite crawl delays.
- Add robots.txt respect before crawling at scale.